⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Space Pirates
node MET · MET · ⟦The Space Pirates:MET:1e3b44⟧

WHO   — The Space Pirates — the raider-race
WHAT  — The enemy host of the Metroid universe — the marauding army that holds planet Zebes, guards Mother Brain, and turns the life-draining Metroids into weapons, opposed in the 8-bit original and again in Super Metroid.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because they hunger for the Metroids' power to end all life and bend the galaxy to Mother Brain; because raiding, conquest, and the harvesting of living weapons are the whole of their nature.
HOW   — By overwhelming numbers and the Zebesian rank-and-file, by Ridley and Kraid as their dragon-captains, by the fortress-warrens of Zebes, and by the stolen Metroid larvae they nurture and arm in Tourian under Mother Brain's command.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We took her world and her kin — and we made of Zebes a fortress; but the hunter comes alone into the dark, and the Metroids we stole will be our ruin.

spoken token : photh-vaeth-maem   ·   hex : 1e3b44
